originalText.text:
When I called I found out he doesn't take insurance patients and I can only afford insurance rates. But he took the time to tell me about the types of psychiatrists I might find on the list of in-network psychiatrist from the insurance company and was willing to go through some names on it to see if anyone he would recommend is on the list- on a separate phone call from the initial phone call I made AFTER I said I cannot book an appointment with him for financial reasons.

I never had things like this happen to me when I call doctors of any kind, and if I could afford this doctor I would have gone to see him. If you can afford to pay out of pocket for a good doctor, I would recommend this person. I wasn't even his patient and he made me feel like I was cared for. That is very rare.

originalText.text: Dr. Kahn is by far the most kind, knowledgeable, and trusted psychiatrist I have seen in my 30 years of treatment. Possessing an excellent “bedside” manner, his assessment process and just being “in-tune” with me are what matters most. He is highly skilled, professional, reliable, and he tells funny jokes, an attribute that I enjoy. I highly recommend Dr. Kahn for medication management or psychiatric care combined with medication management. I love him and hope he never retires. I told him that if/when he did, I would still like to see him!
